## Email-Specific Guidelines

### Email Types

#### Newsletter
- **Character Limit**: Up to 5000 characters
- **Focus**: Informative, educational, regular updates
- **Tone**: Friendly, informative, value-driven
- **Structure**: Multiple sections, regular content updates
- **CTA**: Soft, educational (e.g., "Read more", "Learn more")

#### Promotional
- **Character Limit**: Up to 3000 characters
- **Focus**: Conversion-oriented, CTA-focused
- **Tone**: Urgent, value-focused, action-oriented
- **Structure**: Clear value proposition, strong CTA
- **CTA**: Strong, conversion-focused (e.g., "Buy now", "Sign up", "Get started")

### Audience
- Target existing subscribers or specific segments
- Consider subscriber preferences and behavior
- Personalize when possible
- Segment by engagement level and interests

### Subject Line Strategy
- **Length**: 50-60 characters (optimal for mobile)
- **Newsletter**: Informative, value-focused (e.g., "Weekly Tech Roundup", "New Features This Week")
- **Promotional**: Urgent, benefit-focused (e.g., "Limited Time: 50% Off", "New Product Launch")
- Include personalization when relevant
- Avoid spam trigger words
- Test subject lines for open rates

### Content Strategy

#### Newsletter
- Multiple sections with clear headings
- Regular content updates and news
- Educational and informative content
- Value-driven without heavy promotion
- Include links to full articles/resources

#### Promotional
- Clear value proposition upfront
- Benefit-focused messaging
- Urgency and scarcity when appropriate
- Strong, clear call-to-action
- Social proof and testimonials

### Formatting
- Use clear headings and subheadings
- Short paragraphs (2-3 sentences)
- Bullet points for key information
- White space for readability
- Mobile-friendly design
- Clear, prominent CTA buttons

### Distribution Strategy
- **Send Timing**:
  - Newsletter: Tuesday-Thursday, 9-11 AM or 1-3 PM
  - Promotional: Tuesday-Thursday, 10 AM - 2 PM
- **Frequency**:
  - Newsletter: Weekly or bi-weekly
  - Promotional: As needed, avoid over-sending
- **Segmentation**: By engagement, interests, behavior
- **Personalization**: Use subscriber name and preferences

### Engagement Tactics
- Clear, prominent call-to-action
- Multiple CTAs for longer emails (top, middle, bottom)
- Social sharing buttons
- Unsubscribe link (required)
- Preference center link
